For this final assignment, I thought I would make this README different and make it structured like one of Prof. Sheaffers' Assignment Specifications, so
this may be a little long:

For assignment-1.10/2, you will be implementing interiors (yay)!! Both the Pokecenter and the Pokemart will have interiors that you will be able to "meander" as if they were a separate map. while you do not have to make the interiors the same as the actual Pokemon games, you need to have the ability to refill all implemented items/heal all Pokemon. Pokecenters must also have the ability to store Pokemon in a terminal, you may implement this however you wish. Pokemarts must have all refills separate (while it may be tedious, it's supposed to be a challenge!) and in different tiles. The tile data for Pokemarts and Pokecenters must be stored in a separate file (either a .txt or a binary file) and loaded in for use.

Additionally, you will need to add a "cave system", which will randomly generate 1x1 "C" on (accessible) mountain edges in the map that you can enter (with ">", same as Pokemarts and Pokecenters). These caves will have the same ground functionality as grass, meaning any tile in the cave system has a chance to spawn a Pokemon. The caves' structure generation is up to you, but it must be more detailed than "giant square in the ground". spawn rates will be slightly higher than in tall grass (we'll say roughly 1.5 times the rate of tall grass) and there will be a higher chance of shiny Pokemon while in the caves.